Independence statement
----------------------
ForThePeople UK is not affiliated with any government body, political
party, or campaign. It is a citizen-facing dashboard over publicly
available data.

Data sources
------------
This dashboard aggregates public data from UK government and
open-data sources. Each upstream has its own licence; the derived
content on the dashboard inherits those licences:

- Office for National Statistics (ONS) — Open Government Licence v3.0
  <https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/doc/open-government-licence/version/3/>
- gov.uk datasets — Open Government Licence v3.0
- NHS Digital — Open Government Licence v3.0 (most datasets)
- Department for Education (DfE) — Open Government Licence v3.0
- Police.UK — Open Government Licence v3.0
- Met Office MIDAS / Open Data — Open Government Licence v3.0
- Open-Meteo — Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0)
  <https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/>
- postcodes.io — Open Government Licence v3.0 (wraps ONS ONSPD data)
  <https://postcodes.io/>
- gov.uk announcements (Atom feed) — Open Government Licence v3.0
  <https://www.gov.uk/government/announcements.atom>
- BBC News UK (RSS feed, headlines + links only) — BBC rights, used
  under standard RSS aggregation practice with link-back attribution.
  <http://feeds.bbci.co.uk/news/uk/rss.xml> |
  <https://www.bbc.co.uk/usingthebbc/terms/>

Under OGL v3.0 and CC BY 4.0, attribution to the upstream source is
required on any redistribution of the derived data. BBC headlines
are displayed as-is with a direct link to the source article, per
standard RSS aggregation practice. The dashboard attributes every
metric to its source inline; contributors must preserve those
attributions.

Analysis code, caching, validation, and the Streamlit UI are
separately licensed under Apache 2.0 (see LICENSE).

